7. why no deep diagnostics

- With only 200 samples and a Random Forest model, deep statistical diagnostics (normality, homoscedasticity, VIF, significance tests, interaction effects) are unnecessary. Random Forest makes no distributional assumptions, handles non-linearity and collinearity natively, and captures interactions automatically. Limited sample size also makes many tests unreliable. Focus on cross-validation and feature importance instead.

    


